attributes.title: Animal Planet GO - Watch TV Shows Online

attributes.description: Victims working graveyard shifts are thrust into real-life nightmares.
attributes.longDescription: Experience true stories of victims working graveyard shifts who are thrust into real-life nightmares as killers lie in wait to strike.
attributes.name: Dead of Night

attributes.description: Antonio Ballatore builds spaces for pets and the people they love.
attributes.longDescription: Antonio Ballatore, his right-hand bulldog, Chewie, and a team of Catsperts and Barkitects transform drab, cramped homes and outside areas into functional, high-style spaces for both pets and the people they love.
attributes.name: Animal Cribs

attributes.description: Josh Gates and his team investigate the realms beyond the "unknown."
attributes.longDescription: Josh Gates has decided it's time to finally explore the dark side of our world. He has picked Jessica Chobot and Phil Torres to mount unprecedented expeditions into the unexplained and perhaps...unexplainable.
attributes.name: Expedition X

attributes.description: Viewers are taken behind the scenes of Atlanta's Georgia Aquarium.
attributes.longDescription: Viewers are taken behind the scenes and given all-access to the largest aquarium in the Western Hemisphere -- Atlanta's Georgia Aquarium.
attributes.name: The Aquarium: A Deeper Dive

attributes.description: A behind-the-scenes look reveals the lives of animals at the San Diego Zoo.
attributes.longDescription: This behind-the-scenes series reveals the daily lives of animals and the people that care for them at the San Diego Zoo and the San Diego Zoo Safari Park, as well as the San Diego Zoo Institute for Conservation Research.
attributes.name: The Zoo: San Diego - A Look Inside

attributes.description: The hidden secrets of iconic structures around the globe are revealed.
attributes.longDescription: The hidden secrets of iconic structures and monuments from around the globe are revealed through scientific investigation and CGI animation.
attributes.name: Unearthed

attributes.description: Forrest Galante heads to the Maldives to find a supposedly extinct shark.
attributes.longDescription: With Sharkmania facts and bonus scenes. Forrest Galante heads to the Maldives to find a supposedly extinct shark. Forrest dives deep to determine once and for all whether the Pondicherry shark is extinct or alive.
attributes.name: Extinct or Alive

attributes.description: Evil casts a shadow over the lives of those it touches.
attributes.longDescription: Evil Lives Here: Shadows of Death reveals how the impact of a crime changes people, and what follows that life-changing event. Anchored by intimate POV interviews, this original series explores how a crime forever alters the lives of those involved.
attributes.name: Evil Lives Here: Shadows of Death

attributes.description: Witness the death-defying exploits of two extraordinary alligator trappers.
attributes.longDescription: Follow the death-defying exploits of Paul Bedard and Jimmy Riffle, two alligator trappers who risk injury and death to hand-capture alligators that have invaded the back yards, swimming pools, garages and bedrooms of Florida Everglades residents.
attributes.name: Gator Boys

attributes.description: Daniel Villegas confessed to killing two teens, but it may have been a lie.
attributes.longDescription: In 1993, 16-year-old Daniel Villegas confessed to killing two teenagers in El Paso, Texas. He was sentenced to life in prison. But what if it was all a lie? What if Daniel was forced to confess to a shooting he knew nothing about?
attributes.name: A Fatal Confession: Keith Morrison Investigates

attributes.description: Everything's bigger in Texas, including the job of the Texas Game Wardens.
attributes.longDescription: The elite force of Texas Game Wardens protects and patrols more than a quarter million square miles of the Lone Star State’s natural resources, which is filled with deserts, lakes, piney woods, bayous, plains and coast.
attributes.name: Lone Star Law

attributes.description: Experts uncover subterranean phenomena around the world.
attributes.longDescription: Experts uncover subterranean phenomena around the world, and share their impressive stories, unique origins and important roles in history, along with the secrets they still keep hidden underground.
attributes.name: Underground Marvels

attributes.description: Jeremy Wade hunts for freshwater fish with a taste for human flesh.
attributes.longDescription: This rip-roaring ride through the dark side of nature mixes action and adventure with mysteries. Watch as Jeremy Wade deconstructs exactly how these river monsters are built to kill.
attributes.name: River Monsters

attributes.description: Follow Robert Irwin as he helps to rescue and relocate animals in need.
attributes.longDescription: Get an up-close-and-personal look at Australia Zoo, and the animals who call it home, with Robert Irwin.
attributes.name: Crikey It's the Irwins: Robert to the Rescue

attributes.description: Experts analyze mysteries caught on tape that seem to defy explanation.
attributes.longDescription: A team of experts analyze surveillance footage to uncover the science behind some of the most bizarre occurrences ever caught on camera.
attributes.name: Strange Evidence

attributes.description: Scientists and enthusiasts brace for a season of storm chasing each spring.
attributes.longDescription: Every spring, changing weather patterns on the Great Plains, also known as Tornado Alley, create a recipe for catastrophe, and a collection of scientists and enthusiasts brace for a season of storm chasing.
attributes.name: Storm Chasers

attributes.description: This documentary tells the definitive story of the Civil War.
attributes.longDescription: This documentary tells the definitive story of one of the most extraordinary and bloodiest chapters in American history. The series uses six of the war's most significant battles to illuminate the bigger themes and lesser-known stories.
attributes.name: Blood and Fury: America's Civil War

attributes.description: Dr. Paul Calle discusses Nadia, the tiger who tested positive for COVID-19.
attributes.longDescription: The Zoo gives audiences a behind-the-scenes look at the Bronx Zoo. With full access to its 265-acre campus, located just 10 miles from Times Square, we shine a light on a world of more than 6,000 animals and the 500-plus people who care for them.
attributes.name: The Zoo

attributes.description: A man and a woman battle extreme environments without clothes.
attributes.longDescription: What happens when you put two complete strangers - sans clothes - in some of the most extreme environments on Earth? Each male-female duo is left with no food, no water, no clothes, and only one survival item.
attributes.name: Naked and Afraid

attributes.description: A rescue center gives pit bulls and parolees a second chance at life.
attributes.longDescription: Tia Maria Torres and her family at the Villalobos Rescue Center work tirelessly to change the stereotypes surrounding pit bulls. Parolees are offered a second chance and volunteer their time finding these canines a forever home.
attributes.name: Pit Bulls & Parolees: Found a Forever Home

attributes.description: The biggest aquarium manufacturer in the US creates over-the-top tanks.
attributes.longDescription: Acrylic Tank Manufacturing, the biggest aquarium manufacturer in the US, creates over-the-top aquariums for a wide array of clients. Up to 50,000 gallons in size, the tanks hold some of the world's most unusual and quirky fish.
attributes.name: Tanked Jr.

attributes.description: A rescue center gives pit bulls and parolees a second chance at life.
attributes.longDescription: Tia Maria Torres and her family at the Villalobos Rescue Center work tirelessly to change the stereotypes surrounding pit bulls. Parolees are offered a second chance and volunteer their time finding these canines a forever home.
attributes.name: Pit Bulls & Parolees: Waiting for a Forever Home

attributes.description: The veterinarians share their most intense experiences.
attributes.longDescription: The veterinarians of Cy-Fair Animal Hospital share their most intense experiences working with animals and their owners in the Houston area.
attributes.name: The Vet Life: Extreme Animal Encounters

attributes.description: Body Cam captures the up-close and dangerous world of police officers.
attributes.longDescription: Raw, intense, and action-packed, Body Cam uses body camera footage to show the dangerous, fast-moving situations officers face and the life-or-death decisions they must make in the blink of an eye.
attributes.name: Body Cam

attributes.description: The Raneys use their expertise to help people who live off the grid.
attributes.longDescription: Marty, Matt and Misty Raney use their building, farming and hunting expertise to help people who strive to live off the grid.
attributes.name: Homestead Rescue

attributes.description: Uncover the true stories surrounding history's greatest mysteries.
attributes.longDescription: Host Jamie Theakston attempts to uncover the true stories surrounding the great treasures, long-held conspiracy theories, ancient relics and lost civilizations that are often omitted from the history books.
attributes.name: Forbidden History

attributes.description: The Irwin family documents life at the Australia Zoo.
attributes.longDescription: Steve Irwin's legacy lives on via his wife Terri and children Bindi and Robert. As passionate wildlife conservationists, they care for over 1,200 animals daily at the Australia Zoo, its world-class wildlife hospital and on expeditions across the globe.
attributes.name: Crikey! It's the Irwins

attributes.description: Game wardens patrol more than 18-million acres of Maine's rugged terrain.
attributes.longDescription: In Maine, the elite Game Warden Services patrols more than 18-million acres of rugged terrain. For the wardens, hunting season brings poachers, dangerous wildlife and intense search-and-rescue missions.
attributes.name: North Woods Law

attributes.description: Who killed Caylee Anthony?
attributes.longDescription: Get a look inside the lies, betrayal and murder that form the foundation of the Caylee Anthony case. New interviews with Caylee's grandparents detail the events surrounding the 2-year-old's tragic death.
attributes.name: Casey Anthony: An American Murder Mystery

attributes.description: In Nome, Alaska, miners search for gold on the bottom of the Bering Sea.
attributes.longDescription: In Nome, Alaska, the gold rush is on. Driven by gold fever and sometimes desperate need, miners pilot their ragtag dredges and dive with hoses to suck up gold from the bottom of the frigid, unpredictable Bering Sea.
attributes.name: Bering Sea Gold

attributes.description: A rescue center gives pit bulls and parolees a second chance at life.
attributes.longDescription: Tia Maria Torres and her family at the Villalobos Rescue Center work tirelessly to change the stereotypes surrounding pit bulls. They offer second chances to parolees as they volunteer and fight to find these canines a forever home.
attributes.name: Pit Bulls & Parolees

attributes.description: A behind-the-scenes look reveals the lives of animals at the San Diego Zoo.
attributes.longDescription: From the producers who brought you The Zoo comes an all-new series, The Zoo: San Diego, with an all-access look at the San Diego Zoo and Safari Park, voted #1 zoo in the world.
attributes.name: The Zoo: San Diego

attributes.description: Explore the fascinating world of how items are manufactured.
attributes.longDescription: Explore the fascinating world of how everyday items are manufactured and produced. From aluminum foil to contact lenses, discover how many of the things we buy and use are made.
attributes.name: How It's Made

attributes.description: Jonathan and Angela Scott document big cats in the Maasai Mara Reserve.
attributes.longDescription: Jonathan and Angela Scott document the lives of lions, leopards and cheetahs living in the Maasai Mara National Reserve in Kenya.
attributes.name: Big Cat Tales

attributes.description: Experts investigate the crimes, investigation and impact of BTK.
attributes.longDescription: The horrible crimes of serial killer BTK held Wichita on razor's edge for three decades before he was finally captured. What was almost as shocking as the ten murders he committed was the apparently normal family man that he was.
attributes.name: BTK: Chasing A Serial Killer

attributes.description: Christmas celebrations, extra gold mining and dangerous Alaska moments.
attributes.longDescription: Discovery families get into the Christmas spirit, the Gold Rush crew shares behind-the-scenes footage from their time on the road and Alaska's most intense, jaw-dropping and gut-wrenching moments are revealed.
attributes.name: Alaska: The Last Frontier

attributes.description: The biggest aquarium manufacturer in the US creates over-the-top tanks.
attributes.longDescription: Acrylic Tank Manufacturing, the biggest aquarium manufacturer in the US, creates over-the-top aquariums for a wide array of clients. Up to 50,000 gallons in size, the tanks hold some of the world's most unusual and quirky fish.
attributes.name: Tanked

attributes.description: Too Cute! tells the coming-of-age stories of cuddly baby animals.
attributes.longDescription: Too Cute! tells the coming-of-age stories of cuddly baby animals. From their unsteady first steps to their new adventures in the world, these babies are simply too lovable, too curious and too cute to quit.
attributes.name: Too Cute!

attributes.description: Explore unusual phenomena captured by satellites orbiting Earth.
attributes.longDescription: Hundreds of satellites orbit Earth and capture the world like it's never been seen before, sometimes revealing objects and phenomena that defy explanation. Explore these unusual images as scientists explain the mysteries.
attributes.name: What on Earth?

attributes.description: Who is the killer hiding among your friends and neighbors?
attributes.longDescription: A brutal attack seems isolated, but investigators soon discover it's only the tip of an iceberg. Acts of revenge, serial killings and webs of deceit leave communities in fear as real-life devils in disguise are revealed.
attributes.name: Devil Among Us

attributes.description: See No Evil reveals how surveillance cameras solve murders.
attributes.longDescription: See No Evil reveals how the deadliest crimes are solved by the only witnesses that never lie -- and where murderers have no place to hide: surveillance cameras.
attributes.name: See No Evil

attributes.description: Never-before-seen footage looks into the eyes of killers hiding among us.
attributes.longDescription: Monsters can be found lurking behind any innocent smile and on any street corner in America. Never-before-seen-video footage stares straight into the eyes of these killers who hide in plain sight.
attributes.name: American Monster

attributes.description: From shorthairs to snowshoes, meet many different breeds of cats.
attributes.longDescription: Get to know all the details of our favorite feline breeds in this encyclopedic series on cats.
attributes.name: Cats 101

attributes.description: Revisit some of the most brutal killers in modern history.
attributes.longDescription: This harrowing series revisits some of the most brutal killers in modern history, reviewing news footage and the words of the killers themselves to see which terrifying traits each killer exhibited. What are the signs...of evil?
attributes.name: Signs Of A Psychopath

attributes.description: The true accounts of people who ventured deep into the forest alone.
attributes.longDescription: These are the true accounts of people who ventured deep into the forest only to come screaming out with stories that defy reality.
attributes.name: These Woods Are Haunted

attributes.description: A paranormal investigation team explores the most haunted towns in America.
attributes.longDescription: A paranormal investigation team travels across America to explore the country's most haunted towns and investigate the stories that have spooked locals for generations.
attributes.name: Haunted Towns

attributes.description: Anthony Bourdain uncovers the best in cuisine across the world.
attributes.longDescription: Anthony Bourdain uncovers the best cuisine across the world. At each location, Tony dives headfirst into life's colorful and rich pageant, bringing his intellectual curiosity, empathy, wit and boundless appetite.
attributes.name: Anthony Bourdain: No Reservations

attributes.description: Erin and Ben Napier revitalize their small town's historic homes.
attributes.longDescription: Husband-and-wife team Erin and Ben Napier bring their small Mississippi hometown back to life with modern and affordable updates to its historic homes.
attributes.name: Home Town

attributes.description: The most notorious female killers are profiled by Candice DeLong.
attributes.longDescription: Crime experts explore the motives and modus operandi of female killers. While males are often driven by anger, impulse and destruction, women usually have more complex, long-term reasons to kill.
attributes.name: Deadly Women

attributes.description: Investigative series of murder cases told by retired detective, Joe Kenda.
attributes.longDescription: Homicide Hunter is a riveting non-fiction investigative series of murder cases told through the personal experience of retired detective, Lieutenant Joe Kenda.
attributes.name: Homicide Hunter: Joe Kenda

attributes.description: Amanda Giese rescues animals with disabilities around the country.
attributes.longDescription: Amanda Giese, founder of Panda Paws rescue in rural Washington State, makes it her mission to save animals with disabilities around the country.
attributes.name: Amanda to the Rescue

attributes.description: Veterans who survived battle relive stories of the harsh realities of war.
attributes.longDescription: Against the Odds features stories of real-life bands of brothers who exhibited unparalleled bravery, solidarity and endurance on the battlefield. Reliving battles from WWII, Korea, Vietnam and Iraq, these are true stories of the harsh realities of war.
attributes.name: Against the Odds

attributes.description: Patients battle parasitic creatures that have taken over their bodies.
attributes.longDescription: It's a life or death battle between modern medicine and evolution as patients fight off the stealthy, cunning parasitic creatures that have taken up residence inside their unsuspecting bodies.
attributes.name: Monsters Inside Me

attributes.description: Eyewitnesses share their terrifying true tales of the paranormal.
attributes.longDescription: Terrifying true stories of the paranormal are told by the people who experienced them. The mystery of each haunting is unraveled through first-person accounts and dramatic re-enactments, revealing that life and death are far stranger than ever imagined.
attributes.name: A Haunting

attributes.description: A team of trappers hunt down legendary beasts in the Appalachian Mountains.
attributes.longDescription: A team of  trappers hunt down legendary beasts in the Appalachian Mountains. These mysterious creatures are on the run as the skilled outdoorsman follow a trail of fresh evidence and gather testimony from eyewitnesses.
attributes.name: Mountain Monsters

attributes.description: The Wolfpack chases faith, family and freedom in the remote wilderness.
attributes.longDescription: Born and raised wild, the Brown Family overcomes nature's obstacles as they struggle for faith, family and freedom in the remote wilderness.
attributes.name: Alaskan Bush People

attributes.description: Zak Bagans and his crew investigate the most haunted places in the world.
attributes.longDescription: Zak Bagans and his crew investigate the most haunted places in the world. During the dusk-to-dawn lockdown, key evidence is documented to uncover the truth behind paranormal activity.
attributes.name: Ghost Adventures

attributes.description: Every suspect shares a last name in these homespun murder mysteries.
attributes.longDescription: Every family has skeletons in the closet. This true-crime series investigates homespun murder mysteries where everyone is a suspect, and every suspect shares a last name.
attributes.name: Blood Relatives

attributes.description: Paranormal explorers face their fears at haunted locations.
attributes.longDescription: Maverick paranormal explorer Dakota Laden takes his sister and best friend on a cross-country road trip to face their deepest, darkest fears at the most-haunted locations in America.
attributes.name: Destination Fear

attributes.description: Four eccentric but passionate investigators search for Bigfoot.
attributes.longDescription: From small towns in the South to remote areas of the Pacific Northwest, four eccentric but passionate investigators embark on one single-minded mission to find the elusive creature known as Bigfoot.
attributes.name: Finding Bigfoot

attributes.description: Incredible engineering projects that are now abandoned are revisited.
attributes.longDescription: The world's most incredible engineering projects are revisited to uncover why places full of mysteries and untold secrets are now abandoned ruins.
attributes.name: Mysteries of the Abandoned

attributes.description: Facing a global pandemic, seven captains must unite to save the fishery.
attributes.longDescription: Facing a global pandemic, half the fleet is tied up leaving a handful of boats to catch the fleetwide quota or face closure of the fishery. At sea, seven fiercely independent captains must work together to save their way of life and the American dream.
attributes.name: Deadliest Catch

attributes.description: Get up close and personal with a variety of popular dog breeds.
attributes.longDescription: This is the most comprehensive dog encyclopedia on television. With over 800 dog breeds recognized worldwide, this series spotlights the adorable, the feisty and the unexpected.
attributes.name: Dogs 101

attributes.description: Experts analyze footage from eye-opening and terrifying paranormal videos.
attributes.longDescription: A panel of experts analyze footage from some of the world's most eye-opening and terrifying paranormal videos. From poltergeist activity to lights in the sky, these firsthand accounts just might turn skeptics into believers.
attributes.name: Paranormal Caught on Camera

attributes.description: Dr. Jeff & team give hope to pets and the people who love them.
attributes.longDescription: There's no such thing as a regular day at Denver's Planned Pethood Plus veterinary clinic. For clients and their pets, Dr. Jeff Young and his team represent one last hope, and possibly the difference between life and death, for both pets and wild animals.
attributes.name: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet

attributes.description: See the inner workings of the cosmos, including black holes and beyond.
attributes.longDescription: How was it built and how does it actually work? With a cast of experts and eye-popping CGI, we're looking under the celestial hood to tell the greatest story of all -- the story of where we and everything else came from.
attributes.name: How the Universe Works

attributes.description: The last residents of the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge try to survive.
attributes.longDescription: The last remaining residents of the vast and remote Arctic National Wildlife Refuge struggle to survive the rugged terrain and frigid conditions.
attributes.name: The Last Alaskans

attributes.description: Jackson Galaxy helps families on the verge of giving up their felines.
attributes.longDescription: Armed with more than 15 years of experience, a proven training program and his signature guitar case filled with cat toys, Jackson Galaxy is on a mission to help cat owners find the source of conflict with their furry friends.
attributes.name: My Cat From Hell

attributes.description: Josh Gates investigates the world's most iconic and captivating legends.
attributes.longDescription: Josh Gates investigates the truth behind the world's most iconic and captivating legends. Leaving no stone unturned, his adventures take him around the globe as he immerses himself in the core locales linked to each tale.
attributes.name: Expedition Unknown

attributes.description: Cameras capture the remarkable behavior of the animals at Chester Zoo.
attributes.longDescription: Venture to Chester Zoo, the most popular zoo in Britain. This observational documentary series uses micro-rig camera technology to capture, in incredible detail, the remarkable behavior of the animals there.
attributes.name: The Secret Life of the Zoo

attributes.description: Paula Zahn unravels shocking crimes interviewing those closest to the case.
attributes.longDescription: Veteran journalist Paula Zahn steps out of the studio and into the field to unravel criminal investigations, tracking the drama of each story by featuring the opinions of those closest to the case.
attributes.name: On The Case with Paula Zahn

attributes.description: A paranormal investigator uncovers the truth behind small town hauntings.
attributes.longDescription: Filmmaker and paranormal investigator Steve Shippy uncovers the truth behind small town hauntings in America's heartland.
attributes.name: Haunting in the Heartland

attributes.description: A team of monster hunters search for Bigfoot in Texas and Louisiana.
attributes.longDescription: Gulf Coast Bigfoot Research Organization (GCBRO) founders Bobby Hamilton and  Jim Lansdale lead a team of commandos on a mission to find and kill a Bigfoot in order to prove its existence to science.
attributes.name: Bigfoot is Real

attributes.description: Experts attempt to unlock the mystery of the Alaska Triangle.
attributes.longDescription: Experts and eyewitnesses attempt to unlock the mystery of the Alaska Triangle, a remote area infamous for alien abductions, Bigfoot sightings, paranormal phenomena and vanishing airplanes.
attributes.name: The Alaska Triangle

attributes.description: Experts explore extraordinary happenings that science can't explain.
attributes.longDescription: Experts and eyewitnesses explore some of the most-extraordinary happenings in recent history that science can’t explain.
attributes.name: World's Most Unexplained

attributes.description: Tense trials trigger explosions of emotion and violence in the courtroom.
attributes.longDescription: Chaos in Court is a show that goes beyond and behind clips of dramatic, unexpected and cathartic courtroom moments.
attributes.name: Chaos in Court

attributes.description: UFO experts investigate extraterrestrial activity across America.
attributes.longDescription: Former Colorado deputy sheriff Chuck Zukowski and his team search for definitive proof of extraterrestrial life as they investigate reports of UFO-related incidents across America.
attributes.name: Alien Highway

attributes.description: Venture to Victoria, Australia to visit one of the world's oldest zoos.
attributes.longDescription: This new series captures the special relationship between the extraordinary animals and their passionate keepers at one of the planet’s largest and oldest zoos, spread across three stunning locations in Victoria, Australia.
attributes.name: Mega Zoo

attributes.description: Experts explore America's greatest unsolved mysteries.
attributes.longDescription: America's greatest unsolved mysteries are explored through interviews, archival footage and re-creations. Recently unearthed evidence and intriguing, new theories bring each case closer than ever to finally being solved.
attributes.name: American Mystery

attributes.description: It's game time! Join Martha and Snoop for Puppy Bowl XVII.
attributes.longDescription: It's the annual fur-tastic battle on the grand gridiron of Puppy Bowl Stadium. Celebrating all that is right with the world, Puppy Bowl is the pinnacle of competition, cuteness and pet rescue.
attributes.name: Puppy Bowl

attributes.description: An elite team of Bigfoot experts go on the hunt for the elusive beast.
attributes.longDescription: An elite team of Sasquatch specialists journey into the unforgiving North American wilderness to prove once and for all that the elusive beast known as Bigfoot is real.
attributes.name: Expedition Bigfoot

attributes.description: Astronaut Mike Massimino takes a look at the planets of the solar system.
attributes.longDescription: Astronaut Mike Massimino takes an in-depth look at the planets of the solar system, the newly discovered Planet 9, exoplanets and more.
attributes.name: The Planets and Beyond

attributes.description: The epic rise and fall of football star Aaron Hernandez
attributes.longDescription: This absorbing true-crime series takes a fresh look at shocking and well-publicized mysteries -- with exclusive interviews, recent developments, and critical updates coming together to produce inspired new theories in the search for truth and justice.
attributes.name: Aaron Hernandez: An ID Murder Mystery

attributes.description: John Beal hires Richart Sowa and his son to build a floating island.
attributes.longDescription: John Beal is ready to leave the city behind and embrace a life off the grid in Isla Mujeres, Mexico. He hires Richart Sowa and his son, Eden, to build an eco-friendly private floating island made from recycled plastic bottles.
attributes.name: Building Off the Grid

attributes.description: Experts hunt for the truth behind infamous monsters and their origins.
attributes.longDescription: Haunting creatures come to life in a hunt for the truth about infamous monsters and their origins. Experts explore the latest evidence and eyewitness encounters while unveiling mind-blowing theories about these nightmarish beasts.
attributes.name: In Search of Monsters

attributes.description: Discover the lives of men and women protecting the Louisiana wildlife.
attributes.longDescription: A documentary series following the men and women of the Louisiana Department of Fish and Game as they patrol one of the most mysterious and beautiful places on earth; the state of Louisiana.
attributes.name: Louisiana Law

attributes.description: Zak Bagans uncovers the chilling stories behind possessed objects.
attributes.longDescription: Zak Bagans finds macabre objects from around the world and uncovers their terrifying stories. Once they are proven authentic, these cursed items will find a permanent place of resting in Zak's Haunted Museum in Las Vegas.
attributes.name: Deadly Possessions

attributes.description: Specialists harness a digital forensics lab to solve ancient mysteries.
attributes.longDescription: Ancient investigations turn tech as specialists harness an advanced digital forensics lab and use the latest scientific discoveries to solve the biggest mysteries of ancient history.
attributes.name: Ancient Unexplained Files

attributes.description: Military conflicts of the 20th century are examined through key battles.
attributes.longDescription: Great military conflicts of the 20th century are examined through key battles and turning points in combat operations ranging from Pearl Harbor and the Vietnam War to the Cold War and Operation Desert Storm.
attributes.name: Bullet Points

attributes.description: The American Civil War is brought to life.
attributes.longDescription: The American Civil War is brought to life through the personal and horrifying accounts of soldiers from both sides of the conflict. CIVIL WAR: BLOOD ON THE BATTLEFIELDS chronicles the epic struggle for the fate of the nation in a three-part series that follows two proud regiments.
attributes.name: Civil War: Blood on the Battlefield

attributes.description: Witnesses and victims reveal the impact of three US mass shootings.
attributes.longDescription: In the United States, there is an active shooter incident every 12 days. This documentary examines that reality from a new perspective as wounded survivors and grieving relatives from three recent massacres relive the moment their lives changed forever.
attributes.name: In Memoriam

attributes.description: Experts help pets with embarrassing behavioral or health problems.
attributes.longDescription: A team of experts help desperate owners from across the UK with their beloved pets' embarrassing behavioral or health problems.
attributes.name: Embarrassing Pets

attributes.description: Aileen Wuornos' life story told through letters to her best friend.
attributes.longDescription: Aileen Wuornos, America's first female serial killer, wrote down her life story for her childhood best friend Dawn Botkins. In a candid interview, Dawn reveals the contents of those letters to tell the public what really happened.
attributes.name: Aileen Wuornos: Mind of a Monster

attributes.description: This series explores incredible natural phenomena occurring on our planet.
attributes.longDescription: From luminescent waves crashing ashore to mysterious fairy circles as far as the eye can see, this series explores the incredible natural phenomena occurring on our planet.
attributes.name: Impossible Planet

attributes.description: Veterans recall the crucial 72 hours following the invasion in Normandy.
attributes.longDescription: The Day After D-Day is D-Day plus three, the crucial 72 hours following the June 6th invasion as told by combat veterans who fought in the villages, beaches, hedgerows and bridgeheads of Normandy.
attributes.name: Day After D-Day

attributes.description: A multi-season exploration of Yellowstone National Park and its wildlife.
attributes.longDescription: Nestled deep in the Rocky Mountains of the American west is a place unlike anywhere else on the planet. Yellowstone National Park is home to hundreds of animals that have adapted to survive in a harsh and dynamic landscape.
attributes.name: Yellowstone Journals

attributes.description: Untold tales of the heroic souls who brought legendary outlaws to justice.
attributes.longDescription: The violent crime sprees of outlaws like Dillinger, Cassidy and Capone are legendary. But there are two sides to every story, and the heroic tales of the people who brought these criminals to justice deserve to be told.
attributes.name: Natural Born Outlaws

attributes.description: Competitors race to turn mystery ingredients into extraordinary meals.
attributes.longDescription: Competitors race to turn mystery ingredients into extraordinary three-course meals. This competition is all about skill, speed and ingenuity -- and only one chef will impress the judges enough to survive the chopping block.
attributes.name: Chopped: Volume 3

attributes.description: In a world where sharks rule… the best thing about summer is here!
attributes.longDescription: From unbelievable breaches to star-studded encounters, these are the awesome shark moments you’ve been waiting for all year. The biggest blockbuster event of the summer is packed with groundbreaking science, close encounters and unmissable moments.
attributes.name: Shark Week

attributes.description: Biologist Jeremy Wade investigates unsolved mysteries in dark waters.
attributes.longDescription: Angler and biologist Jeremy Wade uncovers the bizarre, the weird and the mysterious as he investigates baffling, unsolved mysteries beneath the surface of dark waters.
attributes.name: Jeremy Wade's Dark Waters

attributes.description: Explore the connections between the minds of Einstein and Hawking.
attributes.longDescription: Albert Einstein and Stephen Hawking were revolutionary thinkers who changed everything known about the universe, and using the latest discoveries, experts explore the connections between these two great minds.
attributes.name: Einstein and Hawking: Unlocking the Universe

attributes.description: A rescue center gives pit bulls and parolees a second chance at life.
attributes.longDescription: Tia Maria Torres and her family at the Villalobos Rescue Center work tirelessly to change the stereotypes surrounding pit bulls. Parolees are offered a second chance and volunteer their time finding these canines a forever home.
attributes.name: Pit Bulls & Parolees: Harrowing Rescues

attributes.description: Get a behind-the-scenes look at the Bronx Zoo, a leader in conservation.
attributes.longDescription: A behind-the-scenes look is offered of the Bronx Zoo, a New York institution and global leader in animal care and species conservation.
attributes.name: The Zoo: From the Inside

attributes.description: Celebrated cop Joe Kenda presents mind-blowing cases from across the US.
attributes.longDescription: This true-crime series hosted by Lt. Joe Kenda, one of America's toughest detectives, features incredibly disturbing and mind-blowing cases from across the country. Lt. Kenda expertly guides us through the complex twists and turns of these bizarre crimes.
attributes.name: American Detective With Lt. Joe Kenda

attributes.description: Stream what you love, all in one place. Start your free trial today!
attributes.longDescription: discovery+ is here, the only streaming service with the greatest real-life entertainment from your favorite TV brands - including HGTV, Food Network, TLC, ID and more - and personalities, plus exclusive originals. Start your free trial today!
attributes.name: discovery+ Preview

attributes.description: A detective tries to outwit one of history's most demented serial killers.
attributes.longDescription: Det. Rick Buckner suspects that long-haul trucker Keith Jesperson may be the Happy Face Killer, one of history's most disturbed serial murderers. Now, the detective must play a deadly cat-and-mouse game to prove Jesperson is the crazed killer they seek.
attributes.name: The Happy Face Killer: Mind of a Monster

attributes.description: Marine experts explore lost shipwrecks and reveal their incredible stories.
attributes.longDescription: Countless shipwrecks lost in the depths of the oceans are each a time capsule containing tales of adventure and tragedy; now, marine experts are the hunt to locate these forgotten ships, explore their secrets and unlock their incredible stories.
attributes.name: Abandoned: Expedition Shipwreck

attributes.description: Michael “Bare Hands” Beran saves wildlife caught in peculiar situations.
attributes.longDescription: Join Michael “Bare Hands” Beran and his eclectic employees as they travel across the country to rescue wildlife caught in peculiar situations. From a coyote in a homeowner’s garage to a skunk in a hot tub - they’ve caught it all with their bare hands.
attributes.name: Bare Hands Rescue

attributes.description: The team sets out to examine compelling Squatch evidence in OH and WV.
attributes.longDescription: The Finding Bigfoot team reunites after three years to investigate compelling Squatch evidence in Ohio and West Virginia. Equipped with the latest technology, including state-of-the-art thermal drones, they set out to prove these creatures are real.
attributes.name: Finding Bigfoot: The Search Continues

attributes.description: Newly released documents reveal shocking secrets about aliens on Earth.
attributes.longDescription: Newly released documents and firsthand accounts of close encounters reveal shocking secrets the US government has been hiding from us for decades. What to do these extraterrestrial visitors want? Do they come in peace, or is it an invasion?
attributes.name: Alien Encounters Declassified

attributes.description: Expert teams create spooky edible displays for the chance to win $50,000.
attributes.longDescription: Cake decorators, sugar artists and pumpkin carving experts battle it out as they create Halloween-themed edible displays. The last team to scare off the competition will take home a $50,000 grand prize.
attributes.name: Halloween Wars

attributes.description: Discover the shock and heart behind vets helping pets with extreme cases.
attributes.longDescription: Discover the shock and heart behind vets transforming pets with extreme cases. At Gatorland, Dr. Jackie operates on Predator the alligator. Later, Dr. Grant diagnoses a pup’s melon-sized growth, and Dr. Cody pops an oozing cyst on Archie the cow.
attributes.name: Pop My Pet

attributes.description: American detectives reveal their most haunting homicide cases.
attributes.longDescription: This series chronicles the harrowing pursuits of American detectives caught amid tragic murder cases that threaten to push them to the brink. These heroic detectives fight for justice, while the indelible moments within will leave them forever changed.
attributes.name: Detective Diaries

attributes.description: Fidel Castro employed a vast spy network that helped him remain in power.
attributes.longDescription: Fidel Castro was one of the most notorious political figures of the 20th Century. Those who worked for and against him reveal the inner workings of the vast spy network that allowed him to remain in power.
attributes.name: Castro: The World’s Most Watched Man

attributes.description: British farmers reveal the challenges and rewards that come with the job.
attributes.longDescription: Three British farmers trying to run three very different family farms across the UK reveal the challenges and rewards that come with making a living off the land.
attributes.name: Born Mucky: Life on the Farm

attributes.description: Forrest Galante uncovers dangerous mysteries of the animal world.
attributes.longDescription: Forrest Galante and his team scour the globe to investigate mysterious creatures at the heart of deadly animal/human conflicts. After solving each mystery, Forrest focuses on resolving the conflict, often saving human and animal lives in the process.
attributes.name: Mysterious Creatures with Forrest Galante

attributes.description: Jessica Chobot and Phil Torres dive into the mysterious legend of Mothman.
attributes.longDescription: Jessica Chobot and Phil Torres dive into the legend of Mothman by searching for clues in a long-sealed bunker and a top-secret Air Force base.
attributes.name: Mothman Phenomenon

attributes.description: Robert swims with Gloria, a large reticulated python for the first time.
attributes.longDescription: Robert gets in the water with Gloria, a 12-foot reticulated python, to swim alongside her for the first time in the Crocoseum. Then, Bindi welcomes home two orphaned kangaroo joeys, and Terri helps the release of an animal.
attributes.name: Robert's Python Swim

attributes.description: The team investigates the terror inside a former Pennsylvania poorhouse.
attributes.longDescription: The team heads to Pennsylvania to investigate a former home for the destitute and elderly. Dakota is determined to conquer the terror inside, but things go horribly wrong when Alex leaves the property in a dire paranormal-induced emergency.
attributes.name: Hill View Manor

attributes.description: A camel faces new challenges as he ages and a red panda welcomes two cubs.
attributes.longDescription: Max the camel faces new challenges as he ages. The Zoo prepares to give an injured turkey vulture a permanent home, but after healing, there may be a change of plan. Willow the red panda gives birth to two baby cubs.
attributes.name: A New Beginning

attributes.description: A functionally extinct species of turtle finds new life.
attributes.longDescription: A charismatic ostrich named Olga works to be reunited with her flock. Buster the squirrel monkey is introduced to the Zoo's troop of feisty females. A functionally extinct species of turtle finds new life and everyone's favorite warthog is back.
attributes.name: The Great Turtle Comeback

attributes.description: Power tools are needed for an Amur tiger's root canal.
attributes.longDescription: The staff is hopeful for a successful breeding season when Mshango the giraffe meets the females of the herd. Power tools are needed for an Amur tiger's root canal, while Louie the swan falls ill, jeopardizing his release with his partner-in-crime Dewey.
attributes.name: Tiger's Day at the Dentist

attributes.description: A woman's mangled body is found beside a lonely stretch of highway.
attributes.longDescription: A woman's body is found beside a lonely stretch of highway. When the coroner suspects foul play, Kenda is called in to solve the second homicide case of his career.
attributes.name: My Second Case

attributes.description: Caylee Anthony's grandparents detail their granddaughter's disappearance.
attributes.longDescription: Casey Anthony insists that her 2-year-old daughter, Caylee, was abducted by the nanny, but investigators soon discover the child has been missing for 31 days. Caylee's grandparents share details of the tragic events.
attributes.name: Little Girl Lost

attributes.description: Josh is on the trail of the legendary lost treasure of a notorious pirate.
attributes.longDescription: Josh Gates takes on the Indian Ocean's punishing waters as he chases the lost treasure of Olivier Levasseur, aka "The Buzzard," rumored to be worth more than a billion dollars.
attributes.name: The Fortune of the Buzzard

attributes.description: The team heads to Wisconsin for the first time ever in search of Sasquatch.
attributes.longDescription: The team heads to Wisconsin for the first time ever in search of Sasquatch. Enlisting help from locals, their final night investigation is taken to new heights when they are stalked by Bigfoots in the dark.
attributes.name: Brews, Brats and Bigfoots

attributes.description: A team is deployed on Mt. Monadnock where a severed finger is found.
attributes.longDescription: When a hiker finds a severed finger, Officer Hannett and NH State Police team up to investigate. A bear hunter makes a surprising confession to Officer Masucci. And, Officer Towne’s patrol is interrupted by a call from his son’s school principal.
attributes.name: Mountaintop Mystery

attributes.description: A hunter pleads ignorance when caught with tree stands on private property.
attributes.longDescription: A deer hunter pleads ignorance when caught with tree stands on private property. Officer Crouse catches a group of ATV speedsters, and Officer MacFazden investigates a suspicious bear kill.
attributes.name: Trail Blazers

attributes.description: Jeremy comes face-to-face with the monstrous eastern snakehead.
attributes.longDescription: Jeremy ventures in search of the eastern snakehead, a predator fish invading North American waters.  Known for being able to breathe air and crawl on land, Jeremy dives into its lair to have a face-to-face encounter.
attributes.name: Killer Snakehead

attributes.description: Robert takes on the challenging task of relocating an aggressive croc.
attributes.longDescription: Robert takes on the challenging task of relocating Bosco, the most aggressive croc at the zoo. Bindi must investigate Forest the giraffe's bad knee problem, and Terri helps Harley the koala find love.
attributes.name: Bosco the Croc's Big Move

attributes.description: Jeremy uncovers the truth behind flesh-eating fish.
attributes.longDescription: Jeremy Wade travels to the Amazon River determined to discover the truth behind flesh-eating fish.
attributes.name: Amazon Flesh Eaters

attributes.description: An baby's illness leaves her paralyzed and doctors race to find the cause.
attributes.longDescription: When an infant contracts a mysterious illness that leaves her paralyzed, doctors race to discover the cause. Then, doctors rush to save the eyesight of a young father and uncover a monster that's nearly impossible to kill.
attributes.name: The Organ Shredder

attributes.description: The team investigates reports of rampant Bigfoot activity in California.
attributes.longDescription: The search for Bigfoot brings the team to Southern California, where reports have been rampant. They zero in on the canyons of Deep Creek, enlisting the help of a local for a night investigation that yields proof that Sasquatches live there.
attributes.name: Bright Lights and Bigfoots

attributes.description: The Kilchers kick it into high gear as they prepare for the fall.
attributes.longDescription: As fall approaches, the Kilchers kick into high gear. A large bull moose stalks the homestead and Eivin must keep his family safe. Atz Sr. hunts bear and nearly loses a horse. Otto begins the massive cleanup from an explosive wildfire prevention project.
attributes.name: Backyard Prey

attributes.description: Two cousins are separated by a cold-blooded murder.
attributes.longDescription: Mark Corona and Paul Stoeppler are two cousins who are as close as brothers. This blood bond is destroyed when one of them is murdered in cold blood. Never-before-seen home video and shocking CCTV footage reveal what really happened.
attributes.name: Brothers in Arms

attributes.description: Ken tries a new perspective to find new ground.
attributes.longDescription: Shawn gets his first taste of the shifting seabed. Ken tries a new perspective to find new ground. Kris and Emily each try out greenhorn divers to boost their productivity, but the plan grinds to a halt for one of them.
attributes.name: Sweet Child o' Mining

attributes.description: Josh joins Jess and Phil to track down a half-man, half-beast in Wisconsin.
attributes.longDescription: Josh Gates is on the ground with Jessica Chobot and Phil Torres to chase reports of a half-man, half-beast in rural Wisconsin. Frequent attacks and new sightings of the infamous Beast of Bray Road have left locals crippled with fear for three decades.
attributes.name: An American Werewolf

attributes.description: A slew of poached bird eggs is found while searching for a missing person.
attributes.longDescription: A slew of poached birds is discovered on an abandoned boat, changing a missing person's search into a hunt for a hiding poacher. Game Wardens Mike Boone and Lauren Iles rescue a tangled 12-foot gator, while multiple boats are inspected on Lake Limestone.
attributes.name: Marshland Massacre

attributes.description: An infant falls into a catatonic-like state and suffers numerous seizures.
attributes.longDescription: An infant falls into a catatonic-like state before suffering a frightening number of seizures. As doctors scramble to save his life, they discover he's the victim of an infection that's on the rise.
attributes.name: The Monster in My Mouth

attributes.description: The crew heads to Arizona to investigate the world-famous London Bridge.
attributes.longDescription: Zak and the crew head to Lake Havasu, Arizona, to investigate one of the most-famous bridges in the world. A dark paranormal energy engulfs the massive structure, attracting death, despair and even the ghost of Jack the Ripper!
attributes.name: London Bridge

attributes.description: Ben and Erin Napier transform a tired house for one of their close friends.
attributes.longDescription: A photographer and close friend of the Napier's is looking for a traditional home with a touch of modern style. After deciding on a classic mansion in need of a complete makeover, Ben and Erin transform the tired house into a show-stopping home.
attributes.name: A New Beginning

attributes.description: The Irwins release animals into the Australian Outback.
attributes.longDescription: Carrying three baby kangaroos and an emu, the Irwins caravan into the Australian Outback to release the animals on Mourachan, their giant wildlife conservation property.
attributes.name: Road Trip Rescue

attributes.description: Doctors discover a mysterious parasitic species inside a man's nose.
attributes.longDescription: A man sees a doctor complaining of agonizing facial pain, and when they investigate, they discover a strange parasitic species living deep in the man's nose; footage of the grisly encounter reveals what happened next.
attributes.name: Mystery of the Face Parasite

attributes.description: A fearsome wolf-like creature could be an Ice Age beast.
attributes.longDescription: Footage of a fearsome wolf-like creature in the remote wilderness of northern Canada could be evidence of a dire wolf, a prehistoric beast that went extinct at the end of the last Ice Age; experts use cutting-edge tech to investigate if it has returned.
attributes.name: Revenge of the Monster Wolf

attributes.description: Game wardens intervene when an overloaded boat and jet skiers risk lives.
attributes.longDescription: Game Wardens Mallory Mitchell and Jeremy Lindsey intervene when an overloaded boat and unruly jet skiers put lives at risk. Game Warden Randolph McGee investigates reports of a wild hog being tortured, while other game wardens round up a willy alligator.
attributes.name: Wake of Destruction

attributes.description: Tia lends a hand when Lizzy struggles to balance her work-home life.
attributes.longDescription: Now a mother of two, Lizzy leans on Tia to help find a work-life balance. A California couple hopes to adopt a dog comfortable in the pool, and Mariah’s mission to save an injured dog abandoned in the rain leads her to something completely unexpected.
attributes.name: Mother of Chaos

attributes.description: The VRC crew race to catch a dog on the run.
attributes.longDescription: On the streets of New Orleans, the VRC crew is on a mission to catch a runaway dog. A Californian family wants a new furry family member, a paralyzed pup named Polly takes a trip to the vet, and Mariah pitches a fundraising idea to the parolees.
attributes.name: Evading Capture

attributes.description: Lizzy and Toney rescue a trio of orphaned dogs.
attributes.longDescription: VRC is at its limit when the amount of rescues and drop-offs rise. Lizzy and Toney travel to a remote part of the city to save a trio of orphaned dogs in a dire state, veteran tenant Lil Rocky faces a cancer scare, and a litter of puppies are welcomed.
attributes.name: Life in a Cage

attributes.description: On Cannon Cliffs, an emergency team is deployed on a heroic rescue mission.
attributes.longDescription: A horrific rock climbing accident on Cannon Cliffs sends two officers and an emergency team on a heroic helicopter rescue mission. A combative man is found illegally riding an OHRV and is questioned by Officer Crouse, and a moose causes a traffic jam.
attributes.name: Cliff Face Crisis

attributes.description: A pair pushing 50 and a pair in their 20s take on the Sonoran Desert.
attributes.longDescription: Four survivalists -- a pair who are pushing 50 and a pair in their early 20s -- are dropped into the Sonoran Desert. Tested by mountain lions, gila monsters and unrelenting heat, does experience bring wisdom or will youth be served?
attributes.name: Okay, Boomer

attributes.description: Four carnivore chefs are ready to crush it in a battle featuring pork.
attributes.longDescription: Four carnivores are ready to crush it, and the pork battle begins with a double helping of piggy goodness in the first basket. The entree basket includes some fancy mushrooms, and the judges giddily approve of the meaty candy bar in the dessert basket.
attributes.name: Battle of the Meats: Pork!

attributes.description: Jeremy heads to Japan to uncover the truth behind two extraordinary fish.
attributes.longDescription: Jeremy heads to Japan to uncover the truth behind two extraordinary fish. Known as the Namzu and the Kappa, these mysterious creatures have made a name for themselves as being sinister killers, and Wade is eager to catch them.
attributes.name: Cold Blooded Horror

attributes.description: Jeremy ventures to New Zealand in search of a legendary fish.
attributes.longDescription: Jeremy Wade ventures to New Zealand in search of legendary fish. Described as a mysterious man-eater over 200 years ago, this freshwater predator may lurk in the remote rivers and deep lakes and Jeremy is determined to find it.
attributes.name: Flesh Ripper

attributes.description: Officers Canfield and Jones use an ROV to search the Merrimack River.
attributes.longDescription: As temperatures drop to near-freezing, Officers Canfield and Jones use an ROV to search Merrimack River for a missing person. Meanwhile, a man is caught illegally releasing coyotes from traps, and officers host a meet-and-greet at the headquarters.
attributes.name: Hidden in the Water

attributes.description: Experts investigate a futuristic tower in the mountain forests of Croatia.
attributes.longDescription: A breathtaking stainless steel tower seems otherworldly and out of place in the remote mountain forests of Croatia; experts investigate and uncover a dark past of Nazi-led conflict and a monument to a desperate fight for survival.
attributes.name: Alien Ghost Tower

attributes.description: On the Bald Mountain Trail, officers help rescue an injured hiker.
attributes.longDescription: On the Bald Mountain Trail, officers help rescue an injured hiker, but the icy trail puts the whole crew at risk. Officer Egan is the first medical responder to a sudden snowmobile crash, and two four-wheelers crash through ice on Webster Lake.
attributes.name: Meltdown

attributes.description: Nambung National Park in Australia is home to some curious formations.
attributes.longDescription: Nambung National Park in Australia is home to some curious formations and a fascinating desert, just minutes from the ocean. Then a permafrost cave in Iceland and an unreal landscape in Turkey are explored.
attributes.name: Nature’s History Unraveled

attributes.description: At an annual fishing tournament, anglers are cited for breaking the law.
attributes.longDescription: At the annual ice fishing tournament in Washington, NH, numerous fishermen are cited for breaking the law. Meanwhile, Officer Canfield catches reckless snowmobilers riding without registrations then receives a call that has him rushing to the hospital.
attributes.name: Snow Patrol

attributes.description: The secrets behind the famous northern and southern lights are revealed.
attributes.longDescription: The secrets behind the famous northern and southern lights are revealed. Then, a series of sink holes in Mexico offer a window to a spectacular underwater cave system, and eternal flames flicker in a New Zealand forest, but never burn it down.
attributes.name: The Secret Behind the Lights

attributes.description: The annual GoNorth Snowfest starts with a bang and ends in citations.
attributes.longDescription: After an abandoned barrel is discovered, Officer Hannett works with local police to see if it’s related to a 20-year-old cold case regarding a missing mother and daughter. Later, the popular GoNorth Snofest starts with a bang and ends in citations.
attributes.name: Abandoned

attributes.description: Hippo Funani welcomes an addition and staff raise an orphaned koala.
attributes.longDescription: A hippo named Funani welcomes an adorable addition to the family. Staff raise an orphaned koala joey named Omeo. And, after developing an innovative milk formula for elephant calves, a team travels to Kenya to monitor the results.
attributes.name: Baby Miracles

attributes.description: The Fish and Game Dive Team searches the water for gravestones and bodies.
attributes.longDescription: When the embankment of the Upper Ammonoosuc River begins to erode near a cemetery, The Fish and Game Dive Team searches the water for gravestones and bodies. A hunter is caught without her license, and a loaded firearm puts lives at risk.
attributes.name: Grave Danger

attributes.description: Michael “Bare Hands” Beran saves wildlife caught in peculiar situations.
attributes.longDescription: Join Michael “Bare Hands” Beran and his eclectic employees as they travel across the country to rescue wildlife caught in peculiar situations. From a coyote in a homeowner’s garage to a skunk in a hot tub - they’ve caught it all with their bare hands.
attributes.name: Bare Hands Rescue

attributes.description: A gazelle surprises the staff after moving into the former hog habitat.
attributes.longDescription: After taking over the former red river hog habitat, a gazelle gives the team a big surprise. Staffers race to prepare a den when they suspect the amur leopard Satka is pregnant, and koalas are nursed back to health after being saved from the bushfires.
attributes.name: Hog Wild

attributes.description: Officers must find the culprit responsible for nearby gunshots.
attributes.longDescription: A report of possible gunshots fired near a Police Chief’s home has Officers on the hunt for answers, but what K9 Moxie discovers leads to a twist in the case. An ATV accident leaves a rider seriously injured, and a rabid racoon puts lives in danger.
attributes.name: Raccoon Rodeo

attributes.description: A white rhino undergoes an intense procedure in order to save the species.
attributes.longDescription: A pair of rescued mountain lion cubs are ready for their new habitat. Staff celebrate when a lappet-faced vulture produces the zoo’s first egg for the species. And Nikita the white rhino undergoes an intense procedure in the hope of saving a species.
attributes.name: Cubs Come Home

attributes.description: The team sets out to examine compelling Squatch evidence in OH and WV.
attributes.longDescription: The Finding Bigfoot team reunites after 3 years to investigate compelling Squatch evidence in Ohio and West Virginia. Equipped with the latest technology, including state-of-the-art thermal drones, they set out to prove these creatures are real.
attributes.name: The Search Continues

attributes.description: The zoo welcomes a pair of playful platypuses for the first time.
attributes.longDescription: Staff develop an innovative course of treatment when cheetah Amara shows signs of injury. The zoo becomes host to the only pair of platypuses outside Australia. And, a new team of falcon trainers show off their skills.
attributes.name: Cheetah on the Run

attributes.description: The teams create displays of Halloween haunts on a road trip.
attributes.longDescription: Six teams consisting of an expert pumpkin carver, a cake artist and a sugar master dive into the first challenge: creating spookily delicious displays of Halloween haunts taking a monster road trip. Actor Jeremy Ray Taylor appears as a guest judge.
attributes.name: Monster Road Trip

attributes.description: A family of ATV riders is busted for breaking the law.
attributes.longDescription: The New Hampshire Fish and Game Dive Team fights harsh conditions while on a double drowning mission at the Merrimack River. Officer Egan rescues a baby owl after the nest is disturbed, and a family of ATV riders are busted for breaking the law.
attributes.name: Dangerous Consequences

attributes.description: At Safari Park, a pair of wallabies become ambassador animals.
attributes.longDescription: When lesser flamingo eggs and chicks are being preyed upon, the team must make a nerve-wracking decision. Wallaby Thelma and her joey Everest become ambassador animals, and a new perch is created for Stuart, the young fishing cat.
attributes.name: Baby Wallaby Debut

attributes.description: Abigail the century-old Galapagos tortoise undergoes surgery.
attributes.longDescription: At the Safari Park, plans are made for tufted deer Poppy and Honeysuckle to meet Draco, a potential mate known for his “fangs.” Brother grizzlies prep for a new diet, and a century-old Galapagos tortoise Abigail undergoes a critical surgery.
attributes.name: Abigail the Incredible

attributes.description: A woman is suspected of being in possession of flying squirrel kits.
attributes.longDescription: In Newton, NH, Officer Letourneau receives an interesting tip about a woman in possession of baby flying squirrels. Things take a turn for Officers investigating an ATV accident, and an OHRV rider is caught trespassing on restricted trails.
attributes.name: Squirrel Showdown

attributes.description: Koala joeys Boomeri and Noorundi become roommates.
attributes.longDescription: The Rhino Rescue Center welcomes Arthur, the southern white rhino calf. A young nyala must be hand-raised before returning to its herd, koala joeys make a big move, and Connor the Malaysian tiger struggles with strange nosebleeds.
attributes.name: Koala Boys

attributes.description: Discover the shock and heart behind vets helping pets with extreme cases.
attributes.longDescription: Discover the shock and heart behind vets transforming pets with extreme cases. At Gatorland, Dr. Jackie operates on Predator the alligator. Later, Dr. Grant diagnoses a pup’s melon-sized growth, and Dr. Cody pops an oozing cyst on Archie the cow.
attributes.name: Pop My Pet

attributes.description: Officer Mancini races to help Officer Holmes after a reckless UTV accident.
attributes.longDescription: When a reckless UTV strikes Officer Holmes from behind, Officer Mancini helps him seek medical treatment while handling the crime scene. A car accident kills a doe leaving two twin fawns vulnerable, and firecrackers give a veteran intense flashbacks.
attributes.name: Officer Down

attributes.description: The meerkat mob must take to a new diet after a mealworm shortage.
attributes.longDescription: The staff hopes for a mating match between the black rhino newcomers, Kendi and Aria. Meanwhile, the zoo cares for an abandoned beaded lizard found in a local yard, a cock-of-the-rock egg hatches, and the meerkat mob are put on a new furry diet.
attributes.name: Dining with Meerkats

attributes.description: Nadia the Malayan tiger tests positive for COVID-19.
attributes.longDescription: The zoo’s medical team must perform critical surgery on a bison calf born with a bowed leg. Three lynx kittens are ready to explore their exhibit, and the first known US case of COVID-19 in animals is confirmed when Nadia the Malayan tiger tests positive.
attributes.name: A New Reality

attributes.description: Troody the young red kangaroo has big shoes to fill.
attributes.longDescription: A keel-billed toucan confiscated from smugglers begins a new life at the zoo. Meanwhile, Troody the young red kangaroo has big shoes to fill, a herd of Bactrian fawns prepares to go on exhibit, and the gorillas enjoy a new form of entertainment.
attributes.name: Bouncing Troody

attributes.description: During Hurricane Ida, Wildlife Agents deploy on search and rescue missions.
attributes.longDescription: As Hurricane Ida makes landfall, Wildlife Agents deploy to help the people of Louisiana. An injured woman is trapped in a flooded hotel, elderly neighbors await rescue in punishing conditions, and lifesaving supplies must be delivered to those in need.
attributes.name: In the Eye of Hurricane Ida

attributes.description: Two young men capture a demonic figure in the mountains of Jordan.
attributes.longDescription: Two young men capture a ghostly figure that begins chasing them on a deserted road in the mountains of Jordan; experts investigate and uncover local tales of black magic practitioners and demonic entities with supernatural powers.
attributes.name: Haunting on Devil Road

attributes.description: Aurora, a skittish Amur tiger, struggles to adjust to her new home.
attributes.longDescription: Rescued harbor seal pup Sydney finds a new family at the New York Aquarium. Zoo staff are challenged when skittish Amur tiger Aurora struggles to adjust to her new home, and a hand-raised red bird-of-paradise chick is reunited with its siblings.
attributes.name: New Cats on the Block

attributes.description: A pest threatens Tom's crops, and Ally tries to save his soya from pigeons.
attributes.longDescription: At Tom’s Cambridgeshire farm, a potent enemy emerges and threatens his wheat harvest. Ally devises a plan in order to save his soya crop from ravenous pigeons, and Ian is determined to ensure a better life for his rescued pigs.
attributes.name: Enemy in the Field

attributes.description: Forrest sets out to stop the crocodile attacks that are plaguing a village.
attributes.longDescription: Rumors of witchcraft bring Forrest to Africa's Zambezi River, the site of crocodile attacks plaguing a local fishing village. He and his childhood friend are determined to stop the killings and save the croc before things turn even more deadly.
attributes.name: Croc Witchcraft

attributes.description: Satellites reveal a symbol carved in Australia's Great Victoria Desert.
attributes.longDescription: Satellite images capture a giant symbol mysteriously carved into the expanse of Australia's Great Victoria Desert; an expert investigation reveals a secret nuclear weapons testing coverup by the British government with numerous aboriginal casualties.
attributes.name: Australia's Nuclear Desert

attributes.description: A gorilla must undergo a critical root canal to fix his tooth problem.
attributes.longDescription: A gorilla must undergo a critical root canal to fix his tooth problem. A red-crested turaco chick fledges the nest, and a pair of puma cubs travel to their new home at the Queens Zoo. Meanwhile, a warthog is trained to receive vaccines with ease.
attributes.name: Cubs in Queens

attributes.description: Rural crime hits Pete and Ally as thieves strike right before harvest.
attributes.longDescription: Tragedy strikes when Pete and Ally’s farm is burglarized right before harvest. Tom’s main worker Joe needs a major attitude check before taking vital exams, and Ian is determined to grow his herd but is faced with a difficult decision.
attributes.name: To Catch a Criminal

attributes.description: The Zoo: San Diego
attributes.longDescription: The staff hopes for a mating match between the black rhino newcomers, Kendi and Aria. Meanwhile, the zoo cares for an abandoned beaded lizard found in a local yard, a cock-of-the-rock egg hatches, and the meerkat mob are put on a new furry diet.
attributes.name: Dining with Meerkats

attributes.description: OWN Spotlight: Where Do We Go From Here?
attributes.name: Part 1

attributes.description: Ghost Adventures
